  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\n<!--     https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md -->\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\n<!--   * Read the debugging docs: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Monitor/Logging/ -->\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3Ahyperledger/Besu -->\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\n\n### Description\nWhen starting besu with a `--data-path` that it is unable to write to, besu gives an unhelpful error message and exits:\n```\n➜  besu git:(heads/main) ✗ build/install/besu/bin/besu --data-path=/not_allowed_to_write_here\n2022-03-04 15:56:10.450-08:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Using LibEthPairings native alt bn128\n2022-03-04 15:56:10.451-08:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Using the native implementation of the signature algorithm\n2022-03-04 15:56:10.453-08:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Starting Besu version: besu/v22.1.2-dev-6f7eeca1/osx-aarch_64/oracle-java-17\n2022-03-04 15:56:10.601-08:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Static Nodes file = /not_allowed_to_write_here/static-nodes.json\n2022-03-04 15:56:10.601-08:00 | main | INFO  | StaticNodesParser | StaticNodes file /not_allowed_to_write_here/static-nodes.json does not exist, no static connections will be created.\n2022-03-04 15:56:10.601-08:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Connecting to 0 static nodes.\n2022-03-04 15:56:10.602-08:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Security Module: localfile\n2022-03-04 15:56:10.609-08:00 | main | INFO  | RocksDBKeyValueStorageFactory | No existing database detected at /not_allowed_to_write_here. Using version 1\nFailed to retrieve the RocksDB database meta version\n\nTo display full help:\nbesu [COMMAND] --help\n```\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n* Besu should provide a better error when it is unable to create/initialize the data-dir\n\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\n1. start besu with a `--data-dir` that the user is unable to write to\n\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\n* Besu provides useful feedback about the problem before exiting \n\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\n* Besu gives a generic error about failing to retrieve the rocksdb meta version, then exits.\n\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?] 100%\n\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\n* Software version: 22.1.x\n\n### Additional Information\n\n",
